### Test Booking Service Endpoints

### 1. Login to get token
# @name login
POST http://localhost:5000/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@taponn.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 2. Get existing services (public)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/v1/booking/5/services

### 2.1 Get single service by ID (public)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/v1/booking/5/services/2

### 3. Create a new service
POST http://localhost:5000/api/v1/booking/5/services
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "service_name": "Hair Cut",
  "description": "Professional hair cutting service",
  "duration_minutes": 30,
  "price": 25.00,
  "buffer_time": 10
}

### 4. Update service (this was the missing endpoint)
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/v1/booking/5/services/1
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "service_name": "Premium Hair Cut",
  "description": "Premium hair cutting service with styling",
  "duration_minutes": 45,
  "price": 35.00,
  "buffer_time": 15
}

### 5. Get services again to verify update
GET http://localhost:5000/api/v1/booking/5/services

### 6. Delete service
DELETE http://localhost:5000/api/v1/booking/5/services/1
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.access_token}}

### 7. Get bookings
GET http://localhost:5000/api/v1/booking/5/bookings
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.access_token}}

### 8. Set availability
POST http://localhost:5000/api/v1/booking/5/availability
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "day_of_week": 1,
  "start_time": "09:00:00",
  "end_time": "17:00:00",
  "is_available": true
}

### 9. Get availability
GET http://localhost:5000/api/v1/booking/5/availability
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.access_token}}